</span></div></summary><div class="sc-fGdjyZ eeuPoR pf-327_ pf-accordion-body" data-pf-expandable="true" data-pf-type="Accordion3.Content"><div class="pf-accordion-display-content"><div data-pf-type="Accordion3.Flex.Content" class="sc-hbKfhP esHkbO pf-328_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-329_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iXzffn kEIevs pf-330_"><p class="sc-brPMkR piylR pf-331_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Our software for the motor, battery, and display could be regularly updated through the Hepha APP.</p><p class="sc-brPMkR piylR pf-333_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">1) Open the Hepha app.<br><br>2) Log in to the Hepha app. There is a QR code for the frame number on the back of the user manual. Scan the QR code to register your bike.<br><br>3) Open the settings page.<br><br>4) Settings: Red dots appear on the right side of the motor software, battery software, display software, and shift assistance.<br><br>5) Click to update.<br><br>6) The red dot disappears: The upgrade is successful.</p><p class="sc-brPMkR piylR pf-335_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">You can download the Hepha APP for free from the Google Play Store and the App Store, and it is available in both English and German.If you have an OTA update, please connect your smartphone to the Hepha display on the e-bike via Bluetooth,then the motor, battery, and drive system can be updated.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></details></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><script>
